<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-08-02"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Haitian sought asylum in legation; was removed by force. Have demanded
                            his return, and apology from Government for invading same. Is to be
                            returned. Please advise me as to surrendering him to authorities.
                            Matters here very critical.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Powell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>